41st United States Presidents George H.W. Bush passed away Friday night at the age of 94. The former American President died in his home in Houston, Texas. Mr Bush suffered a form of Parkinson's disease which forced him to use a wheelchair in his recent years. He had also been in and out of hospital during that time. Mr Bush was the father of the 43rd US President, George W. Bush. He was a member of the Republican party and served as president from 1989 to 1993. The story develops.